DESCRIPTION:

These are completion scripts for rake and cap. They do a minimal setup and then use the same common script. They sport file-caching in .rake_completion and .cap_completion respectivly and automatically expire the cache all 24 hours.

INSTALLATION:

Make a folder named ~/.bash_completion.ruby.d:

  cd
  mkdir .bash_completion.ruby.d

Clone the git repo to this folder:

  cd .bash_completion.ruby.d
  git clone git@github.com:niko/rake_and_cap_completion.git

Add these lines to your ~/.bashrc or ~/.profile:

  complete -C ~/.bash_completion.ruby.d/rake_and_cap_completion/rake_and_cap_completion.rb -o default rake
  complete -C ~/.bash_completion.ruby.d/rake_and_cap_completion/rake_and_cap_completion.rb -o default cap
